2
00:01:55.418 --> 00:01:58.420
Easy. boy.

3
00:02:55.047 --> 00:02:56.881
<i>( Gasps</i>

4
00:03:11.162 --> 00:03:13.331
<i>What do you expect?</i>
<i>They're savages.</i>

5
00:03:13.365 --> 00:03:15.700
One lot steals a goat
from another lot.

6
00:03:15.734 --> 00:03:18.737
before you know it they're ripping
each other to pieces.

7
00:03:18.771 --> 00:03:20.939
I've never seen wildlings
do a thing like this.

8
00:03:20.974 --> 00:03:23.275
I never seen a thing like this.
not ever in my life.

9
00:03:23.310 --> 00:03:26.179
How close did you get?

10
00:03:26.213 --> 00:03:29.148
- Close as any man would.
- We should head back to the wall.

11
00:03:31.685 --> 00:03:33.319
Do the dead frighten you?

12
00:03:33.353 --> 00:03:35.788
Our orders were
to track the wildlings.

13
00:03:35.822 --> 00:03:38.657
We tracked them.
They won't trouble us no more.

14
00:03:38.691 --> 00:03:41.360
You don't think
he'll ask us how they died?

15
00:03:43.296 --> 00:03:45.297
Get back on your horse.

16
00:03:50.269 --> 00:03:52.170
Whatever did it to them
could do it to us.

17
00:03:52.205 --> 00:03:54.172
They even killed
the children.

18
00:03:54.207 --> 00:03:57.276
It's a good thing
we're not children.

19
00:03:58.778 --> 00:04:01.380
You want to run away south.
run away.

20
00:04:01.415 --> 00:04:04.317
Of course they will
behead you as a deserter.

21
00:04:04.351 --> 00:04:06.720
if I don't
catch you first.

22
00:04:08.990 --> 00:04:11.258
Get back on your horse.

23
00:04:11.292 --> 00:04:13.260
I won't say it again.

24
00:04:44.825 --> 00:04:47.360
Your dead men seem
to have moved camp.

25
00:04:47.395 --> 00:04:49.929
They were here.

26
00:04:53.201 --> 00:04:55.569
See where they went.

27
00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:43.218
What is it?

28
00:05:43.253 --> 00:05:45.721
It's...

29
00:07:17.969 --> 00:07:21.969
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Game of Thrones 1x01 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Winter Is Coming</font>
Original Air Date on April 17. 2011

30
00:07:21.994 --> 00:07:25.994
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00ff00>elderman</font> ==

31
00:09:48.161 --> 00:09:51.230
Go on. father's watching.

32
00:09:53.267 --> 00:09:55.168
<i>And your mother.</i>

33
00:10:01.176 --> 00:10:04.546
Fine work as always.
Well done.

34
00:10:04.580 --> 00:10:06.415
Thank you.

35
00:10:06.449 --> 00:10:10.418
I love the detail that you've managed
to get in these corners.

36
00:10:10.453 --> 00:10:12.387
<i>Quite beautiful.</i>

37
00:10:12.422 --> 00:10:14.455
The stitching...

38
00:10:35.479 --> 00:10:38.282
And which one of you
was a marksman at 10?

39
00:10:39.251 --> 00:10:40.818
Keep practicing. Bran.

40
00:10:42.888 --> 00:10:44.922
Go on.

41
00:10:44.957 --> 00:10:47.825
Don't think
too much. Bran.

42
00:10:49.294 --> 00:10:51.361
Relax your bow arm.

43
00:11:03.173 --> 00:11:05.974
Quick. Bran!
Faster.

44
00:11:07.477 --> 00:11:09.545
Lord Stark!

45
00:11:10.580 --> 00:11:12.581
My lady.

46
00:11:13.750 --> 00:11:15.784
A guardsman just
rode in from the hills.

47
00:11:15.819 --> 00:11:18.820
They've captured a deserter
from The Night's Watch.

48
00:11:22.124 --> 00:11:24.493
Get the lads to saddle
their horses.

49
00:11:24.527 --> 00:11:26.561
Do you have to?

50
00:11:26.595 --> 00:11:28.929
He swore an oath. Cat.

51
00:11:28.964 --> 00:11:30.931
The law is law.
my lady.

52
00:11:32.100 --> 00:11:33.934
Tell Bran he's coming too.

53
00:11:35.736 --> 00:11:37.403
Ned.

54
00:11:37.438 --> 00:11:39.772
10 is too young
to see such things.

55
00:11:39.806 --> 00:11:41.573
He won't be a boy forever.

56
00:11:43.476 --> 00:11:45.810
And winter is coming.

57
00:12:04.199 --> 00:12:07.801
Lad. go run back
and get the rest.

58
00:12:12.374 --> 00:12:14.241
White Walkers.

59
00:12:14.275 --> 00:12:17.010
I saw the White Walkers.

60
00:12:17.045 --> 00:12:18.979
White Walkers.

61
00:12:19.013 --> 00:12:22.081
The White Walkers.
I saw them.

62
00:12:30.924 --> 00:12:32.759
I know I broke my oath.

63
00:12:34.028 --> 00:12:35.862
And I know
I'm a deserter.

64
00:12:35.896 --> 00:12:39.599
I should have gone back to the wall
and warned them. but--

65
00:12:39.633 --> 00:12:41.801
I saw what I saw.

66
00:12:41.836 --> 00:12:43.836
I saw the White Walkers.

67
00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:47.574
<i>People need to know.</i>

68
00:12:49.710 --> 00:12:51.578
If you can get word
to my family...

69
00:12:51.612 --> 00:12:54.014
<i>Tell them I'm no coward.</i>

70
00:12:54.048 --> 00:12:56.183
<i>Tell them I'm sorry.</i>

71
00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.768
Forgive me. Lord.

72
00:13:18.672 --> 00:13:21.474
In the name of Robert
of the House Baratheon.

73
00:13:21.508 --> 00:13:23.409
- the first of his name...
- Don't look away.

74
00:13:23.443 --> 00:13:25.183
<i>...King of the Andals</i>
<i>and the first men...</i>

75
00:13:25.184 --> 00:13:26.322
Father will know if you do.

76
00:13:26.347 --> 00:13:29.882
<i>...Lord of the Seven Kingdoms</i>
<i>and protector of the realm.</i>

77
00:13:29.917 --> 00:13:32.652
I. Eddard of the House Stark.

78
00:13:32.687 --> 00:13:35.556
Lord of Winterfell
and warden of the north.

79
00:13:35.590 --> 00:13:38.125
sentence you to die.

80
00:13:52.574 --> 00:13:55.041
You did well.

81
00:14:22.236 --> 00:14:24.170
You understand
why I did it?

82
00:14:24.204 --> 00:14:26.172
Jon said
he was a deserter.

83
00:14:26.206 --> 00:14:28.874
But do you understand
why <i>i</i> had to kill him?

84
00:14:28.909 --> 00:14:30.676
"Our way is the old way"?

85
00:14:32.278 --> 00:14:34.246
The man who passes
the sentence

86
00:14:34.280 --> 00:14:36.014
should swing the sword.

87
00:14:37.083 --> 00:14:39.418
Is it true he saw
the White Walkers?

88
00:14:41.220 --> 00:14:44.290
The White Walkers have been
gone for thousands of years.

89
00:14:44.324 --> 00:14:47.127
So he was lying?

90
00:14:51.066 --> 00:14:53.868
A madman sees what he sees.

91
00:15:19.628 --> 00:15:21.796
What is it?

92
00:15:23.565 --> 00:15:26.234
Mountain lion?

93
00:15:27.536 --> 00:15:29.538
There are no Mountain lions
in these woods.

94
00:16:15.522 --> 00:16:17.523
It's a freak!

95
00:16:18.425 --> 00:16:21.160
It's a direwolf.

96
00:16:29.003 --> 00:16:31.737
Tough old beast.

97
00:16:33.173 --> 00:16:35.941
There are no direwolves
south of the wall.

98
00:16:35.975 --> 00:16:38.109
Now there are five.

99
00:16:38.144 --> 00:16:40.812
You want to hold it?

100
00:16:45.017 --> 00:16:47.518
Where will they go?

101
00:16:47.553 --> 00:16:49.354
Their mother's dead.

102
00:16:49.388 --> 00:16:51.023
They don't belong
down here.

103
00:16:51.057 --> 00:16:52.991
Better
a quick death.

104
00:16:53.025 --> 00:16:54.893
They won't last
without their mother.

105
00:16:54.927 --> 00:16:57.095
- Right. Give it here.
- No!

106
00:16:57.130 --> 00:16:58.863
Put away your blade.

107
00:16:58.897 --> 00:17:01.032
I take orders
from your father. not you.

108
00:17:01.067 --> 00:17:03.868
- Please. father!
- I'm sorry. Bran.

109
00:17:03.903 --> 00:17:05.771
Lord Stark?

110
00:17:05.805 --> 00:17:08.273
There are
five pups...

111
00:17:09.742 --> 00:17:11.609
one for each
of the Stark children.

112
00:17:11.644 --> 00:17:14.446
The direwolf is the sigil of your House.

113
00:17:15.814 --> 00:17:18.016
They were meant
to have them.

114
00:17:22.955 --> 00:17:25.390
You will train them
yourselves.

115
00:17:25.424 --> 00:17:27.392
You will
feed them yourselves.

116
00:17:27.426 --> 00:17:30.462
And if they die.
you will bury them yourselves.

117
00:17:38.670 --> 00:17:40.805
What about you?

118
00:17:41.707 --> 00:17:43.308
I'm not a Stark.

119
00:17:43.342 --> 00:17:45.543
Get on.

120
00:17:54.620 --> 00:17:57.022
What is it?

121
00:18:00.826 --> 00:18:04.796
The runt of the litter--
that one's yours. snow.

122
00:19:04.654 --> 00:19:08.090
As your brother.
I feel it's my duty to warn you:

123
00:19:09.359 --> 00:19:11.393
You worry too much.

124
00:19:11.428 --> 00:19:14.763
- It's starting to show.
- And you never worry about anything.

125
00:19:16.466 --> 00:19:20.036
<i>When we were seven</i>
<i>and you jumped off</i>
<i>the cliffs at Casterly Rock.</i>

126
00:19:20.070 --> 00:19:22.405
100-foot drop into the water.

127
00:19:22.439 --> 00:19:24.507
and you were never afraid.

128
00:19:24.542 --> 00:19:27.243
There was nothing to be afraid of
until you told father.

129
00:19:27.277 --> 00:19:29.144
"We're lannisters.

130
00:19:29.178 --> 00:19:31.646
Lannisters
don't act like fools."

131
00:19:33.316 --> 00:19:35.583
<i>What if Jon Arryn</i>
<i>told someone?</i>

132
00:19:35.618 --> 00:19:37.918
But who would he tell?

133
00:19:37.953 --> 00:19:41.088
- My husband.
- If he told the King. both our heads

134
00:19:41.123 --> 00:19:43.323
would be skewered
on the city gates by now.

135
00:19:44.859 --> 00:19:47.862
Whatever Jon Arryn
knew or didn't know. it died with him.

136
00:19:47.896 --> 00:19:51.699
And Robert will choose a new
Hand of the King-- someone to do his job

137
00:19:51.733 --> 00:19:54.635
while he's off fucking boars
and hunting whores--

138
00:19:54.670 --> 00:19:57.638
or is it
the other way around?

139
00:19:57.673 --> 00:20:00.074
And life will go on.

140
00:20:00.108 --> 00:20:02.677
You should be
The Hand of the King.

141
00:20:02.711 --> 00:20:05.546
That's an honor
I can do without.

142
00:20:05.581 --> 00:20:07.715
Their days are too long.

143
00:20:07.749 --> 00:20:10.017
their lives are too short.

144
00:20:48.324 --> 00:20:49.991
All these years

145
00:20:50.026 --> 00:20:51.693
and I still feel
like an outsider

146
00:20:51.727 --> 00:20:53.962
when I come here.

147
00:20:53.997 --> 00:20:56.532
You have five
northern children.

148
00:20:56.566 --> 00:20:59.801
You're not an outsider.

149
00:20:59.836 --> 00:21:02.771
I wonder
if the old gods agree.

150
00:21:03.873 --> 00:21:06.775
It's your gods
with all the rules.

151
00:21:11.916 --> 00:21:14.851
I am so sorry. my love.

152
00:21:16.254 --> 00:21:19.790
- Tell me.
- There was a raven from King's Landing.

153
00:21:21.660 --> 00:21:23.361
Jon Arryn is dead.

154
00:21:23.395 --> 00:21:26.064
<i>A fever took him.</i>

155
00:21:28.835 --> 00:21:31.136
<i>I know he was like</i>
<i>a father to you.</i>

156
00:21:33.939 --> 00:21:37.208
- <i>Your sister. the boy?</i>
- They both have their health.

157
00:21:37.242 --> 00:21:39.410
<i>gods be good.</i>

158
00:21:49.154 --> 00:21:52.056
The raven
brought more news...

159
00:21:53.292 --> 00:21:55.393
The King rides
for Winterfell...

160
00:21:55.428 --> 00:21:57.128
with the Queen

161
00:21:57.163 --> 00:21:59.297
<i>and all the rest</i>
<i>of them.</i>

162
00:21:59.332 --> 00:22:02.601
If he's coming
this far north...

163
00:22:03.971 --> 00:22:06.172
There's only
one thing he's after.

164
00:22:06.206 --> 00:22:09.242
You can always say no. Ned.

165
00:22:17.952 --> 00:22:21.689
We'll need plenty of candles
for Lord Tyrion's chamber.

166
00:22:21.723 --> 00:22:23.657
I'm told he reads
all night.

167
00:22:23.692 --> 00:22:25.593
I'm told he drinks
all night.

168
00:22:25.627 --> 00:22:28.930
How much could he possibly drink?
A man of his...

169
00:22:28.964 --> 00:22:30.731
Stature?

170
00:22:30.766 --> 00:22:33.435
We've brought up
eight barrels of ale from the cellar.

171
00:22:33.469 --> 00:22:36.004
- Perhaps we'll find out.
- In any case.

172
00:22:36.038 --> 00:22:38.707
<i>candles.</i>

173
00:22:42.813 --> 00:22:45.882
Why is your mother so dead set
on us getting pretty for the King?

174
00:22:45.916 --> 00:22:48.751
It's for the Queen. I bet.
I hear she's a sleek bit of mink.

175
00:22:48.786 --> 00:22:50.887
I hear the prince
is a right royal prick.

176
00:22:50.921 --> 00:22:52.955
Think of all those
southern girls he gets to stab

177
00:22:52.990 --> 00:22:54.557
with his right
royal prick.

178
00:22:56.325 --> 00:22:58.460
Go on. Tommy.
shear him good.

179
00:22:58.494 --> 00:23:00.963
He's never met a girl he likes better
than his own hair.

180
00:23:37.868 --> 00:23:40.736
Gods. but they grow fast.

181
00:23:43.106 --> 00:23:44.573
Brandon!

182
00:23:44.607 --> 00:23:47.943
I saw the king.
He's got hundreds of people.

183
00:23:47.977 --> 00:23:51.180
How many times
have I told you no climbing?

184
00:23:51.214 --> 00:23:54.082
But he's coming right now--
down our road.

185
00:24:00.923 --> 00:24:03.491
I want you
to promise me.

186
00:24:03.526 --> 00:24:05.293
no more climbing.

187
00:24:09.698 --> 00:24:11.299
I promise.

188
00:24:13.569 --> 00:24:16.539
- Do you know what?
- What?

189
00:24:16.573 --> 00:24:18.874
You always look
at your feet before you lie.

190
00:24:21.545 --> 00:24:24.914
Run and find your father.
Tell him the King is close.

191
00:25:09.027 --> 00:25:12.730
Where's Arya?
Sansa. where's your sister?

192
00:25:22.842 --> 00:25:24.476
- Hey hey hey hey.
- Ohh.

193
00:25:24.510 --> 00:25:26.811
What are you doing
with that on?

194
00:25:29.614 --> 00:25:31.750
Go on.

195
00:25:33.052 --> 00:25:34.853
Move!

196
00:26:56.867 --> 00:26:58.868
Your Grace.

197
00:27:02.874 --> 00:27:04.975
You've got fat.

198
00:27:17.054 --> 00:27:19.689
- Cat!
- Your Grace.

199
00:27:22.893 --> 00:27:25.961
Nine years-- why haven't I seen you?
Where the hell have you been?

200
00:27:25.995 --> 00:27:27.896
Guarding the north
for you. your Grace.

201
00:27:27.931 --> 00:27:30.700
<i>Winterfell is yours.</i>

202
00:27:33.737 --> 00:27:36.173
- Where's the imp?
- Will you shut up?

203
00:27:36.207 --> 00:27:38.909
Who have we here?

204
00:27:38.943 --> 00:27:40.711
You must be Robb.

205
00:27:43.382 --> 00:27:47.018
My. you're
a pretty one.

206
00:27:47.053 --> 00:27:49.020
Your name is?

207
00:27:49.054 --> 00:27:51.622
Arya.

208
00:27:51.657 --> 00:27:54.693
Oh. show us
your muscles.

209
00:27:56.462 --> 00:27:57.963
You'll be a soldier.

210
00:28:00.567 --> 00:28:03.369
<i>That's Jaime Lannister.</i>
<i>the Queen's twin brother.</i>

211
00:28:03.403 --> 00:28:05.605
<i>Would you please shut up?</i>

212
00:28:15.048 --> 00:28:17.249
My Queen.

213
00:28:17.284 --> 00:28:18.918
My Queen.

214
00:28:18.953 --> 00:28:21.154
Take me to your crypt.
I want to pay my respects.

215
00:28:21.188 --> 00:28:23.423
We've been riding
for a month. my love.

216
00:28:23.457 --> 00:28:25.158
Surely the dead can wait.

217
00:28:25.193 --> 00:28:27.160
Ned.

218
00:28:36.336 --> 00:28:38.137
Where's the imp?

219
00:28:41.507 --> 00:28:43.541
Where is our brother?

220
00:28:43.575 --> 00:28:45.776
Go and find
the little beast.

221
00:28:47.880 --> 00:28:50.314
Tell me about
Jon Arryn.

222
00:28:50.348 --> 00:28:52.983
One minute
he was fine and then...

223
00:28:54.219 --> 00:28:56.954
Burned right through him.
whatever it was.

224
00:28:58.156 --> 00:29:00.091
I loved that man.

225
00:29:00.125 --> 00:29:01.459
We both did.

226
00:29:01.493 --> 00:29:04.729
He never had to teach
you much. but me?

227
00:29:04.763 --> 00:29:05.997
You remember me at 16?

228
00:29:06.031 --> 00:29:07.966
All I wanted to do

229
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:10.635
was crack skulls
and fuck girls.

230
00:29:10.669 --> 00:29:13.571
- He showed me what was what.
- Aye.

231
00:29:13.605 --> 00:29:16.941
Don't look at me like that.
It's not his fault I didn't listen.

232
00:29:20.880 --> 00:29:23.214
I need you. Ned--

233
00:29:23.249 --> 00:29:27.152
down at King's Landing. not up here
where you're no damn use to anybody.

234
00:29:28.688 --> 00:29:31.556
Lord Eddard Stark.

235
00:29:31.591 --> 00:29:34.192
I would name you
the Hand of the King.

236
00:29:38.631 --> 00:29:40.699
I'm not worthy
of the honor.

237
00:29:40.733 --> 00:29:44.470
I'm not trying to honor you.
I'm trying to get you to run my kingdom

238
00:29:44.504 --> 00:29:48.040
while I eat. drink and whore
my way to an early grave.

239
00:29:48.074 --> 00:29:50.175
Damn it. Ned. stand up.

240
00:29:51.444 --> 00:29:53.613
You helped me win
the iron throne.

241
00:29:53.647 --> 00:29:55.748
now help me
keep the damn thing.

242
00:29:56.783 --> 00:29:58.784
We were meant
to rule together.

243
00:29:58.818 --> 00:30:02.887
If your sister had lived.
we'd have been bound by blood.

244
00:30:02.922 --> 00:30:05.290
Well. it's not too late.

245
00:30:06.692 --> 00:30:08.627
I have a son.
you have a daughter.

246
00:30:10.363 --> 00:30:12.197
We'll join our Houses.

247
00:30:28.647 --> 00:30:31.649
Did you have to bury her
in a place like this?

248
00:30:33.386 --> 00:30:35.687
<i>She should be</i>
<i>on a hill somewhere</i>

249
00:30:35.722 --> 00:30:38.324
with the sun
and the clouds above her.

250
00:30:38.358 --> 00:30:40.326
<i>She was my sister.</i>

251
00:30:40.360 --> 00:30:43.128
This is where
she belongs.

252
00:30:43.163 --> 00:30:45.698
She belonged with me.

253
00:30:51.071 --> 00:30:54.340
In my dreams.
I kill him every night.

254
00:30:55.875 --> 00:30:58.343
It's done. your Grace.

255
00:30:58.378 --> 00:31:01.013
The Targaryens are gone.

256
00:31:03.016 --> 00:31:05.317
Not all of them.

257
00:31:16.095 --> 00:31:18.196
<i>Daenerys!</i>

258
00:31:21.267 --> 00:31:23.134
Daenerys.

259
00:31:23.169 --> 00:31:25.203
There's our bride-to-be.

260
00:31:26.105 --> 00:31:29.240
Look. a gift
from Illyrio.

261
00:31:30.309 --> 00:31:32.076
Touch it.

262
00:31:32.111 --> 00:31:34.312
Go on.
feel the fabric.

263
00:31:38.951 --> 00:31:41.118
Mmm.

264
00:31:42.286 --> 00:31:45.089
Isn't he a gracious host?

265
00:31:47.259 --> 00:31:49.294
We've been his guests
for over a year

266
00:31:49.328 --> 00:31:51.296
and he's never
asked us for anything.

267
00:31:51.330 --> 00:31:53.065
Illyrio's no fool.

268
00:31:53.099 --> 00:31:55.434
He knows I won't
forget my friends

269
00:31:55.468 --> 00:31:57.503
when I come
into my throne.

270
00:32:01.640 --> 00:32:04.308
You still slouch.

271
00:32:07.946 --> 00:32:10.347
Let them see.

272
00:32:13.436 --> 00:32:16.405
I need you to be
perfect today.

273
00:32:17.807 --> 00:32:19.708
Can you do that for me?

274
00:32:23.113 --> 00:32:25.815
You don't want to wake
the dragon. do you?

275
00:32:27.252 --> 00:32:28.852
No.

276
00:32:35.794 --> 00:32:38.863
When they write the history
of my reign. sweet sister.

277
00:32:38.897 --> 00:32:41.131
they will say
it began today.

278
00:32:46.210 --> 00:32:48.512
Where is he?

279
00:32:48.546 --> 00:32:51.180
The Dothraki are not known
for their punctuality.

280
00:33:04.395 --> 00:33:08.566
Athchomar chomakaan. Khal vezhven.

281
00:33:08.600 --> 00:33:10.535
May I present
my honored guests?

282
00:33:10.569 --> 00:33:14.273
<i>Viserys</i>
<i>of House Targaryen.</i>

283
00:33:14.307 --> 00:33:16.008
<i>the third of his name.</i>

284
00:33:16.043 --> 00:33:19.378
<i>the rightful king of the Andals</i>
<i>and the first men.</i>

285
00:33:19.412 --> 00:33:21.146
<i>and his sister</i>

286
00:33:21.181 --> 00:33:23.816
<i>Daenerys</i>
<i>of House Targaryen.</i>

287
00:33:26.720 --> 00:33:29.188
Do you see
how long his hair is?

288
00:33:29.223 --> 00:33:31.924
<i>When Dothraki are</i>
<i>defeated in combat.</i>

289
00:33:31.958 --> 00:33:35.894
<i>they cut off their braids</i>
<i>so the whole world can</i>
<i>see their shame.</i>

290
00:33:35.928 --> 00:33:39.897
Khal Drogo has
never been defeated.

291
00:33:41.099 --> 00:33:42.900
He's a savage. of course.

292
00:33:42.934 --> 00:33:45.269
<i>but one of the finest</i>
<i>killers alive.</i>

293
00:33:46.538 --> 00:33:48.672
And you will be his Queen.

294
00:33:48.706 --> 00:33:51.341
Come forward. my dear.

295
00:34:31.415 --> 00:34:33.083
Where is he going?!

296
00:34:33.117 --> 00:34:35.652
- The ceremony is over.
- But he didn't say anything.

297
00:34:35.687 --> 00:34:38.121
- Did he like her?
- Trust me. your Grace.

298
00:34:38.156 --> 00:34:40.657
if he didn't like her.
we'd know.

299
00:34:43.661 --> 00:34:45.929
It won't be
long now.

300
00:34:45.963 --> 00:34:47.864
Soon you will cross
the Narrow Sea

301
00:34:47.898 --> 00:34:50.333
and take back
your father's throne.

302
00:34:50.367 --> 00:34:53.268
The people
drink secret toasts

303
00:34:53.303 --> 00:34:55.003
to your health.

304
00:34:55.037 --> 00:34:57.372
They cry out
for their true king.

305
00:35:00.977 --> 00:35:02.845
When will they
be married?

306
00:35:02.879 --> 00:35:06.416
Soon.
The Dothraki never stay still for long.

307
00:35:06.450 --> 00:35:08.985
Is it true they lie
with their horses?

308
00:35:09.020 --> 00:35:12.089
I wouldn't ask
Khal Drogo.

309
00:35:12.124 --> 00:35:13.991
Do you take me
for a fool?

310
00:35:14.025 --> 00:35:15.860
I take you
for a King.

311
00:35:15.894 --> 00:35:19.097
Kings lack the caution
of common men.

312
00:35:19.131 --> 00:35:21.499
My apologies if
I've given offense.

313
00:35:21.533 --> 00:35:23.902
I know how to play
a man like Drogo.

314
00:35:23.936 --> 00:35:26.838
I give him a Queen
and he gives me an army.

315
00:35:26.873 --> 00:35:29.742
I don't want
to be his Queen.

316
00:35:34.115 --> 00:35:36.217
I want to go home.

317
00:35:37.118 --> 00:35:38.585
So do I.

318
00:35:38.620 --> 00:35:41.755
I want us both
to go home.

319
00:35:41.790 --> 00:35:44.090
but they took it from us.

320
00:35:44.125 --> 00:35:45.892
So tell me. sweet sister.

321
00:35:45.927 --> 00:35:48.128
how do we go home?

322
00:35:49.964 --> 00:35:51.531
I don't know.

323
00:35:51.566 --> 00:35:54.568
We go home with an army.

324
00:35:56.204 --> 00:35:59.406
With Khal Drogo's army.

325
00:35:59.441 --> 00:36:02.443
I would let
his whole tribe fuck you--

326
00:36:02.477 --> 00:36:05.680
all 40.000 men
and their horses too

327
00:36:05.714 --> 00:36:07.582
if that's what it took.

328
00:36:24.698 --> 00:36:27.133
Do you think Joffrey
will like me?

329
00:36:27.167 --> 00:36:29.702
What if he thinks
I'm ugly?

330
00:36:29.737 --> 00:36:33.407
Then he is the stupidest prince
that ever lived.

331
00:36:35.743 --> 00:36:38.311
He's so handsome.

332
00:36:38.346 --> 00:36:41.047
When would we be married?
Soon? Or do we have to wait?

333
00:36:41.082 --> 00:36:44.184
Hush now.
Your father hasn't even said yes.

334
00:36:44.218 --> 00:36:46.052
Why would he say no?

335
00:36:46.087 --> 00:36:49.356
He'd be the second most powerful man
in the kingdoms.

336
00:36:49.390 --> 00:36:51.958
He'd have to leave home.

337
00:36:51.993 --> 00:36:54.928
He'd have to leave me.

338
00:36:54.962 --> 00:36:57.965
And so would you.

339
00:36:57.999 --> 00:37:00.600
You left your home
to come here.

340
00:37:00.635 --> 00:37:03.436
And I'd be Queen someday.

341
00:37:04.505 --> 00:37:06.073
Please make father
say yes!

342
00:37:06.107 --> 00:37:07.974
- Sansa--
- Please please!

343
00:37:08.008 --> 00:37:10.944
It's the only thing
I ever wanted.

344
00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:26.927
Fill that up!
Boys. Rodrik. come on.

345
00:37:26.961 --> 00:37:29.229
<i>Come on!</i>

346
00:37:47.715 --> 00:37:50.483
Is he dead yet?

347
00:37:54.255 --> 00:37:56.723
Uncle Benjen.

348
00:37:58.560 --> 00:38:01.028
You got bigger.

349
00:38:01.063 --> 00:38:04.966
Rode all day.
Didn't want to leave you
alone with the Lannisters.

350
00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:06.935
Why aren't you
at the feast?

351
00:38:06.970 --> 00:38:10.005
Lady Stark thought
it might insult the royal family

352
00:38:10.040 --> 00:38:12.241
to seat a bastard
in their midst.

353
00:38:12.276 --> 00:38:14.978
Well. you're always
welcome on the wall.

354
00:38:15.012 --> 00:38:17.213
No bastard was ever
refused a seat there.

355
00:38:17.248 --> 00:38:18.948
So take me with you
when you go back.

356
00:38:18.983 --> 00:38:21.851
- Jon--
- Father will let me if you ask him.

357
00:38:21.885 --> 00:38:24.086
I know he will.

358
00:38:26.556 --> 00:38:28.790
The wall isn't
going anywhere.

359
00:38:28.825 --> 00:38:30.158
I'm ready

360
00:38:30.192 --> 00:38:31.526
to swear your oath.

361
00:38:31.560 --> 00:38:34.262
You don't understand
what you'd be giving up.

362
00:38:34.296 --> 00:38:36.764
We have no families.

363
00:38:36.798 --> 00:38:40.135
- None of us will ever father sons--
- I don't care about that!

364
00:38:41.337 --> 00:38:43.805
You might. if you knew
what it meant.

365
00:38:47.110 --> 00:38:49.345
I'd better get inside.

366
00:38:49.379 --> 00:38:52.048
rescue your father
from his guests.

367
00:38:55.019 --> 00:38:57.087
We'll talk later.

368
00:39:04.928 --> 00:39:07.729
<i>Your Uncle's in</i>
<i>The Night's Watch.</i>

369
00:39:10.700 --> 00:39:13.034
What are you doing
back there?

370
00:39:13.069 --> 00:39:16.237
Preparing for a night
with your family.

371
00:39:20.709 --> 00:39:22.810
I've always wanted
to see the wall.

372
00:39:22.844 --> 00:39:24.579
You're Tyrion Lannister.

373
00:39:24.613 --> 00:39:26.214
the Queen's brother?

374
00:39:26.248 --> 00:39:28.449
My greatest
accomplishment.

375
00:39:28.484 --> 00:39:32.253
And you-- you're Ned Stark's
bastard. aren't you?

376
00:39:35.657 --> 00:39:37.892
Did I offend you?
Sorry.

377
00:39:39.861 --> 00:39:42.463
You are
the bastard though.

378
00:39:43.698 --> 00:39:46.100
<i>Lord Eddard Stark</i>
<i>is my father.</i>

379
00:39:47.469 --> 00:39:49.970
And Lady Stark
is not your mother.

380
00:39:50.004 --> 00:39:52.272
making you the bastard.

381
00:39:54.475 --> 00:39:57.277
Let me give you
some advice. bastard.

382
00:39:58.445 --> 00:40:00.246
Never forget
what you are.

383
00:40:00.281 --> 00:40:02.215
The rest of the world
will not.

384
00:40:02.249 --> 00:40:04.818
Wear it like armor

385
00:40:04.853 --> 00:40:07.388
and it can never
be used to hurt you.

386
00:40:09.024 --> 00:40:12.027
What the hell do you know about
being a bastard?

387
00:40:13.329 --> 00:40:16.732
All dwarves are bastards
in their father's eyes.

388
00:40:38.222 --> 00:40:42.592
You at a feast--
it's like a bear in a trap.

389
00:40:44.428 --> 00:40:46.762
The boy I beheaded--

390
00:40:46.797 --> 00:40:49.365
- did you know him?
- Of course I did.

391
00:40:49.399 --> 00:40:51.501
Just a lad.

392
00:40:51.535 --> 00:40:53.269
And he was tough. Ned.

393
00:40:53.303 --> 00:40:55.071
a true ranger.

394
00:40:55.105 --> 00:40:58.575
Pfft.
He was talking madness.

395
00:40:59.744 --> 00:41:01.979
Said the Walkers
slaughtered his friends.

396
00:41:02.013 --> 00:41:04.581
The two he was with
are still missing.

397
00:41:06.250 --> 00:41:09.419
Hmph.
A wildling ambush.

398
00:41:09.453 --> 00:41:11.087
Maybe.

399
00:41:11.121 --> 00:41:14.657
Direwolves
south of the wall.

400
00:41:14.692 --> 00:41:17.193
talk of The Walkers.

401
00:41:17.227 --> 00:41:19.829
and my brother might be
the next Hand of the King.

402
00:41:19.863 --> 00:41:23.132
Winter <i>is</i> coming.

403
00:41:24.635 --> 00:41:26.535
Winter is coming.

404
00:41:28.071 --> 00:41:31.006
- Uncle Benjen.
- Robb boy.

405
00:41:31.040 --> 00:41:32.641
- How are you?
- I'm good.

406
00:41:36.346 --> 00:41:38.580
Is this your first time
in the north. your Grace?

407
00:41:38.615 --> 00:41:41.751
Yes.
Lovely country.

408
00:41:45.457 --> 00:41:48.859
I'm sure it's very grim
after King's Landing.

409
00:41:50.129 --> 00:41:52.230
I remember how scared I was
when Ned brought me

410
00:41:52.264 --> 00:41:54.499
up here
for the first time.

411
00:41:56.635 --> 00:41:58.369
Hello. little dove.

412
00:41:59.571 --> 00:42:01.739
But you are a beauty.

413
00:42:01.773 --> 00:42:03.874
- How old are you?
- 13. your Grace.

414
00:42:03.909 --> 00:42:06.643
You're tall.
Still growing?

415
00:42:06.678 --> 00:42:08.578
I think so. your Grace.

416
00:42:08.613 --> 00:42:10.847
And have you bled yet?

417
00:42:15.719 --> 00:42:17.419
No. your Grace.

418
00:42:18.789 --> 00:42:20.957
Your dress.
did you make it?

419
00:42:22.259 --> 00:42:25.595
Such a talent.
You must make something for me.

420
00:42:27.365 --> 00:42:30.467
I hear we might share
a grandchild someday.

421
00:42:30.502 --> 00:42:32.737
I hear the same.

422
00:42:32.771 --> 00:42:34.839
Your daughter will
do well in the capital.

423
00:42:34.873 --> 00:42:38.577
Such a beauty shouldn't stay hidden
up here forever.

424
00:42:54.661 --> 00:42:57.964
- Your pardon.
- I hear we might be neighbors soon.

425
00:42:57.998 --> 00:42:59.665
- I hope it's true.
- Yes.

426
00:42:59.700 --> 00:43:01.567
the King has honored me
with his offer.

427
00:43:01.601 --> 00:43:03.102
I'm sure we'll have
a tournament

428
00:43:03.137 --> 00:43:05.104
to celebrate your new title--
if you accept.

429
00:43:05.139 --> 00:43:07.341
It would be good
to have you on the field.

430
00:43:07.375 --> 00:43:09.543
The competition
has become a bit stale.

431
00:43:09.577 --> 00:43:12.313
- I don't fight in tournaments.
- No?

432
00:43:12.347 --> 00:43:13.848
Getting
a little old for it?

433
00:43:13.882 --> 00:43:17.519
I don't fight
in tournaments

434
00:43:17.553 --> 00:43:20.054
because when I fight
a man for real

435
00:43:20.089 --> 00:43:22.323
I don't want him to know
what I can do.

436
00:43:24.159 --> 00:43:25.959
Well said.

437
00:43:26.994 --> 00:43:29.929
Arya!

438
00:43:29.963 --> 00:43:32.565
It's not funny!

439
00:43:32.599 --> 00:43:35.334
<i>She always</i>
<i>does this.</i>

440
00:43:35.368 --> 00:43:37.236
<i>This was</i>
<i>my favorite dress.</i>

441
00:43:37.270 --> 00:43:40.539
She always does it
and it's not funny!

442
00:43:40.574 --> 00:43:42.508
Time for bed.

443
00:43:53.455 --> 00:43:56.524
I'm a Northman.

444
00:43:56.558 --> 00:43:58.960
I belong here with you.
not down south

445
00:43:58.994 --> 00:44:01.496
in that rats' nest
they call a capital.

446
00:44:02.531 --> 00:44:05.265
I <i>won't</i> let him
take you.

447
00:44:06.734 --> 00:44:09.202
The king
takes what he wants.

448
00:44:09.236 --> 00:44:11.804
That's why he's King.

449
00:44:13.273 --> 00:44:16.708
I'll say.
"listen. fat man."

450
00:44:18.110 --> 00:44:20.612
"You are not taking
my husband anywhere.

451
00:44:20.646 --> 00:44:23.048
He belongs to me now."

452
00:44:26.753 --> 00:44:28.754
How did he get so fat?

453
00:44:28.788 --> 00:44:31.623
He only stops eating
when it's time for a drink.

454
00:44:34.493 --> 00:44:37.262
<i>It's Maester Luwin.</i>
<i>my Lord.</i>

455
00:44:38.765 --> 00:44:41.167
Send him in.

456
00:44:43.003 --> 00:44:45.171
Pardon. my Lord.
my Lady.

457
00:44:45.206 --> 00:44:48.041
A rider in the night...

458
00:44:48.075 --> 00:44:50.177
from your sister.

459
00:44:57.852 --> 00:45:00.521
- Stay.
- This was sent from the Eyrie.

460
00:45:06.394 --> 00:45:08.762
What's she doing
at the Eyrie?

461
00:45:08.796 --> 00:45:11.431
She hasn't been back there
since her wedding.

462
00:45:19.941 --> 00:45:21.909
What news?

463
00:45:23.245 --> 00:45:26.014
<i>She's fled</i>
<i>the capital.</i>

464
00:45:28.150 --> 00:45:30.819
She says Jon Arryn
was murdered.

465
00:45:30.854 --> 00:45:32.822
By the Lannisters.

466
00:45:32.856 --> 00:45:35.625
She says the King
is in danger.

467
00:45:35.659 --> 00:45:37.928
She's fresh widowed. Cat.

468
00:45:37.962 --> 00:45:39.963
She doesn't know
what she's saying.

469
00:45:39.997 --> 00:45:42.499
Lysa's head would be
on a spike right now

470
00:45:42.533 --> 00:45:44.701
if the wrong people
had found that letter.

471
00:45:44.735 --> 00:45:47.437
Do you think she would
risk her life--

472
00:45:47.471 --> 00:45:49.105
her son's life--

473
00:45:49.139 --> 00:45:52.609
if she wasn't certain
her husband was murdered?

474
00:45:59.752 --> 00:46:01.652
If this news is true

475
00:46:01.686 --> 00:46:04.689
and the Lannisters
conspire against the throne.

476
00:46:04.723 --> 00:46:08.025
who but you can
protect the King?

477
00:46:08.060 --> 00:46:10.261
They murdered
the last Hand.

478
00:46:10.295 --> 00:46:12.664
Now you want Ned
to take the job?

479
00:46:12.698 --> 00:46:14.532
The King rode
for a month

480
00:46:14.567 --> 00:46:16.601
to ask for
Lord Stark's help.

481
00:46:16.635 --> 00:46:19.270
He's the only one
he trusts.

482
00:46:20.739 --> 00:46:23.876
You swore the King
an oath. my Lord.

483
00:46:23.910 --> 00:46:27.011
He's spent half his life
fighting Robert's wars.

484
00:46:27.046 --> 00:46:29.547
He owes him nothing.

485
00:46:31.383 --> 00:46:34.485
Your father and brother
rode south once

486
00:46:34.519 --> 00:46:37.387
on a King's demand.

487
00:46:39.190 --> 00:46:41.391
A different time.

488
00:46:42.827 --> 00:46:44.894
A different King.

489
00:47:42.857 --> 00:47:44.658
When do I meet
with the Khal?

490
00:47:44.693 --> 00:47:46.560
We need to begin
planning the invasion.

491
00:47:46.595 --> 00:47:49.062
If Khal Drogo has
promised you a crown.

492
00:47:49.096 --> 00:47:51.064
- you shall have it.
- When?

493
00:47:51.098 --> 00:47:53.199
When their omens
favor war.

494
00:47:53.233 --> 00:47:56.502
I piss on Dothraki omens.

495
00:47:56.537 --> 00:47:59.773
I've waited 17 years
to get my throne back.

496
00:48:00.929 --> 00:48:03.964
A small gift.
for the new Khaleesi--

497
00:48:05.200 --> 00:48:07.502
songs and histories
from the Seven Kingdoms.

498
00:48:09.204 --> 00:48:10.604
Thank you. Ser.

499
00:48:12.207 --> 00:48:14.942
Are you from my country?

500
00:48:14.976 --> 00:48:17.144
Ser Jorah Mormont
of Bear Island.

501
00:48:17.179 --> 00:48:19.913
I served your father
for many years.

502
00:48:19.947 --> 00:48:23.049
Gods be good. I hope to always
serve the rightful King.

503
00:48:46.175 --> 00:48:48.777
Dragon's eggs. Daenerys.

504
00:48:48.812 --> 00:48:51.781
from the Shadow Lands
beyond Asshai.

505
00:48:51.815 --> 00:48:54.850
The ages have
turned them to stone.

506
00:48:54.884 --> 00:48:56.986
but they will
always be beautiful.

507
00:48:59.123 --> 00:49:01.425
Thank you. Magister.

508
00:49:51.227 --> 00:49:53.695
She's beautiful.

509
00:49:57.767 --> 00:50:00.135
Ser Jorah.
I don't know how to say

510
00:50:00.170 --> 00:50:02.004
thank you
in Dothraki.

511
00:50:02.039 --> 00:50:04.974
There is no word
for thank you in Dothraki.

512
00:50:25.062 --> 00:50:27.063
Make him happy.

513
00:51:26.325 --> 00:51:28.526
No.

514
00:51:31.563 --> 00:51:33.731
Do you know
the common tongue?

515
00:51:38.170 --> 00:51:40.204
No.

516
00:51:44.076 --> 00:51:46.644
Is "no" the only word
that you know?

517
00:51:47.746 --> 00:51:49.480
<i>No.</i>

518
00:52:17.776 --> 00:52:20.010
Rough night. imp?

519
00:52:20.044 --> 00:52:22.112
If I get through this
without squirting

520
00:52:22.147 --> 00:52:24.548
from one end or the other
it'll be a miracle.

521
00:52:24.582 --> 00:52:26.950
I didn't pick you
for a hunter.

522
00:52:26.984 --> 00:52:30.086
The greatest in the land--
my spear never misses.

523
00:52:31.288 --> 00:52:33.857
It's not hunting
if you pay for it.

524
00:52:41.999 --> 00:52:44.267
Are you as good
with a spear as you used to be?

525
00:52:44.301 --> 00:52:46.836
No. but I'm still
better than you.

526
00:52:49.907 --> 00:52:51.774
I know what I'm
putting you through.

527
00:52:51.809 --> 00:52:53.810
Thank you for saying yes.

528
00:52:55.245 --> 00:52:57.680
I only ask you
because I need you.

529
00:52:58.882 --> 00:53:00.783
You're a loyal friend.

530
00:53:00.818 --> 00:53:04.120
You hear me?
A <i>loyal friend.</i>

531
00:53:04.155 --> 00:53:05.955
The last one I've got.

532
00:53:07.591 --> 00:53:09.759
- I hope I'll serve you well.
- You will.

533
00:53:11.294 --> 00:53:14.230
And I'll make sure you
don't look so fucking grim all the time.

534
00:53:15.498 --> 00:53:17.934
<i>Come on. boys.</i>
<i>let's go kill some boar!</i>

535
00:53:27.878 --> 00:53:30.046
Come on. you.

536
00:54:44.099 --> 00:54:46.368
Are you completely mad?

537
00:54:46.402 --> 00:54:49.304
- He saw us.
- It's all right. it's all right.

538
00:54:49.338 --> 00:54:51.206
- It's all right.
- He saw us!

539
00:54:51.240 --> 00:54:53.509
I heard you
the first time.

540
00:54:57.481 --> 00:54:59.916
Quite the little climber.
aren't you?

541
00:55:01.052 --> 00:55:03.987
- How old are you. boy?
- 10.

542
00:55:04.021 --> 00:55:05.721
10.

543
00:55:14.430 --> 00:55:16.932
The things
I do for love.

544
00:55:26.299 --> 00:55:30.299
